---
description: Git and pull-request rules
alwaysApply: true
---

## Commit rules

- NEVER create commits automatically — commit only when the user explicitly requests it.
- NEVER push to remote without an explicit user request.
- NEVER force-push or run destructive git commands without explicit approval.
- When changes are ready, inform the user and wait. Show `git diff` / `git status` for review first.

## Pull request descriptions

- NEVER mention AI tools (Claude, Copilot, Gemini, Cursor, Codex, etc.) in PR title or body.
- NEVER include change statistics (file count, lines added/removed).
- NEVER add test-plan checklists — there is no QA team to execute them.
- Keep PR descriptions focused on what changed and why.
